Dropdown Automation
------------------
1.Select tag based dropdown
--------------------------
Selenium provides Select class to automate <Select> dropdown

Select sc=new Select(dropdown address);

Is dropdown support multiple options selection?
------------------------------
isMultiple()

Single option selection
--------------------------
selectByValue("")
selectByindex()
selectByVisibleText("")

To get all the options
------------------------
getOptions()







2.Bootstrap/javascript/Autosuggestion dropdown
---------------------------------
Xpath locator

Multiple Selection
--------------------------
https://demoqa.com/select-menu?utm_source=chatgpt.com 

=============================================================
Multiple Window Handling
===========================
1.getWindowHandle():String: parent window SessionId
2.getWindowHandles():Set<String>: All windows Id
3.switchTo(): switch to target(window,alert,frame)

driver.switchTo().window();

Open New Tab/New Window
------------------------------
Selenium 4 version we have command newWindow()
newWindow():WebDriver 

driver.switchTo().newWindow(WindowType.TAB);


driver.switchTo().newWindow(WindowType.WINDOW);

======================================================
Alert
===========
Alert always appear from browser or application side...

Selenium Handle is using Alert interface

Types of Alert
-------------------
1.Simple alert with Ok
2.Confirmation alert
3.Prompt alert

1.you need to switch to the alert
Alert alt=driver.switchTo().alert();

2.then handle

4Methods from Alert interface
---------------------------
1.get the text of alert
getText()

2.click on Ok 
accept()

3.click on cancel
dismiss()

4.enter text into alert(prompt)
sendKeys()


